    <text xml:space="preserve">
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn" rendition="class:83217 maturity:83207">
                <p><lb n="1"/>kumārasa A<unclear>v</unclear>atakamasa tha<supplied reason="lost">bho</supplied><lb n="2"/>maghavadatena nāma kar<unclear>i</unclear><supplied reason="lost">to</supplied>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem>A<unclear>v</unclear>atakamasa</lem>
                        <note>The vertical of what we read as <foreign>ma</foreign> is damaged and might be the product of an attempt to correct it to <foreign>ca</foreign>. However, it is possible to make sense of <foreign>Avatakama</foreign>, as corresponding to Skt. <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">avāptakāma</foreign>.</note>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem>nāma</lem>
                        <rdg source="bib:Ghosh1979_01">omitted</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem>kar<unclear>i</unclear><supplied reason="lost">to</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg source="bib:Ghosh1979_01">kara</rdg>
                        <note><ref target="bib:Ghosh1979_01">Ghosh</ref> suggests to reconstruct <foreign>kara<supplied reason="lost">pito</supplied></foreign>, but we would rather expect the second line to record the name of the artisan who made the pillar. The <foreign>i</foreign> in the last preserved syllable is admittedly very faint and our reading is tentative.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><quote>Pillar of the <foreign>kumāra</foreign> Avattakāma, made by Maghavādatta.</quote></p>
            </div>
